Description: Fix GLSL 4.10 Core Profile compatibility by renaming gl_FragColor
 In GLSL 4.10 (Core Profile), gl_FragColor is a reserved built-in name 
 from the legacy OpenGL 2.x Compatibility Profile. It has been removed 
 in Core Profile and cannot be used as a user-defined output variable, 
 even when declared with the 'out' qualifier.
Generated-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6
Reviewed-by: Nicolas HOUDELOT <nicolas@demosdebs.org>
Applied-Upstream: no
Last-Update: 2026-04-22
